title: High Forest Rents Contribution
description: In 2021, forest rents contributed 18.4% to the GDP of the Solomon Islands, one of the highest percentages globally.

title: High Female Employment Rate
description: In 2024, the employment to population ratio for females aged 15 and over in the Solomon Islands was 81.2%, among the highest in the world.

title: High Tariff Rates on Primary Products
description: In 2022, the Solomon Islands had a tariff rate of 48.84% on primary products, one of the highest globally.

title: High Agricultural Exports
description: In 2018, agricultural raw materials made up 73.3% of the Solomon Islands' merchandise exports, one of the highest proportions worldwide.

title: Low Net Intake Rate in Grade 1
description: In 2018, the net intake rate in grade 1 for the Solomon Islands was only 9.2%, one of the lowest globally.

title: Low Domestic Private Health Expenditure
description: In 2022, domestic private health expenditure per capita in the Solomon Islands was just $3.65, one of the lowest in the world.
